  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once the brown rice is cooked, drain and keep it in the sieve, reserving the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chicken pieces</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side, or until browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, combine the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 75ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> – this is your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for a further 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened - this is your <strong>Chinese chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the roots from the <strong>pak choi</strong> and separate the leaves, discarding the roots</p><p>Chop any <strong>larger leaves</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a high heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> and<strong> pak choi</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to wilt</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>cooked brown rice </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min or until everything is well combined - this is your <strong>veg-packed rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into rounds</p><p>Slice the <strong>Chinese chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lean-chinese-chicken-and-veg-packed-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced Chinese chicken</strong> over the <strong>veg-packed rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle over any<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
